## Request Parameters
<a name="API_waf_GetByteMatchSet_RequestParameters"></a>

For information about the parameters that are common to all actions, see [Common Parameters](CommonParameters.md).

The request accepts the following data in JSON format.

 ** [ByteMatchSetId](#API_waf_GetByteMatchSet_RequestSyntax) **   <a name="WAF-waf_GetByteMatchSet-request-ByteMatchSetId"></a>
The `ByteMatchSetId` of the [ByteMatchSet](API_waf_ByteMatchSet.md) that you want to get. `ByteMatchSetId` is returned by [CreateByteMatchSet](API_waf_CreateByteMatchSet.md) and by [ListByteMatchSets](API_waf_ListByteMatchSets.md).  
Type: String  
Length Constraints: Minimum length of 1. Maximum length of 128.  
Pattern: `.*\S.*`   
Required: Yes

