## Response Elements
<a name="API_waf_GetByteMatchSet_ResponseElements"></a>

If the action is successful, the service sends back an HTTP 200 response.

The following data is returned in JSON format by the service.

 ** [ByteMatchSet](#API_waf_GetByteMatchSet_ResponseSyntax) **   <a name="WAF-waf_GetByteMatchSet-response-ByteMatchSet"></a>
Information about the [ByteMatchSet](API_waf_ByteMatchSet.md) that you specified in the `GetByteMatchSet` request. For more information, see the following topics:  
+  [ByteMatchSet](API_waf_ByteMatchSet.md): Contains `ByteMatchSetId`, `ByteMatchTuples`, and `Name` 
+  `ByteMatchTuples`: Contains an array of [ByteMatchTuple](API_waf_ByteMatchTuple.md) objects. Each `ByteMatchTuple` object contains [FieldToMatch](API_waf_FieldToMatch.md), `PositionalConstraint`, `TargetString`, and `TextTransformation` 
+  [FieldToMatch](API_waf_FieldToMatch.md): Contains `Data` and `Type` 
Type: [ByteMatchSet](API_waf_ByteMatchSet.md) object

